1
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:05,580
- Hey, guys. - Hey.

2
00:00:05,630 --> 00:00:07,000
- Hi. - Hey.

3
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:09,460
We need to talk about something.

4
00:00:09,510 --> 00:00:10,830
Yeah. We don't feel like

5
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:12,530
we can host Thanksgiving this year.

6
00:00:12,710 --> 00:00:14,470
- What... - Are you kidding?

7
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:17,520
Well, it's just with work and the stress of adoption...

8
00:00:17,570 --> 00:00:19,510
...we don't feel like we have the energy.

9
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:20,710
Plus, we don't think it's fair

10
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:23,110
that every year the burden falls on us.

11
00:00:24,130 --> 00:00:26,070
That doesn't sound like you.

12
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:29,540
That's Monica talking.

13
00:00:30,740 --> 00:00:34,200
No, no, we made this decision together.

14
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:36,280
She's putting words in your mouth.

15
00:00:36,690 --> 00:00:38,390
Don't you put words in people's mouths.

16
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:40,200
You put turkey in people's mouths.

17
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:42,730
I can't believe this.

18
00:00:42,780 --> 00:00:44,880
This is Emma's first Thanksgiving.

19
00:00:45,010 --> 00:00:46,250
No, it's not.

20
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:48,590
It's not? When was she born?

21
00:00:50,870 --> 00:00:51,890
Well, personally,

22
00:00:51,940 --> 00:00:54,060
I think it's great you're giving yourself a break.

23
00:00:54,110 --> 00:00:55,460
Thank you, Pheebs.

24
00:00:55,510 --> 00:00:56,900
Sure. It's just as well.

25
00:00:57,050 --> 00:00:58,520
I mean, last year wasn't very good.

26
00:00:58,570 --> 00:01:00,180
I think she's losing her touch.

27
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:03,790
What? You are way off, lady.

28
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,370
Am l? Really? Am l?

29
00:01:05,420 --> 00:01:07,290
Well, why don't you cook Thanksgiving dinner

30
00:01:07,340 --> 00:01:08,590
and prove me wrong.

31
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:11,740
Well, think about it.

32
00:01:11,790 --> 00:01:13,950
You'd be trying to top what you did last year.

33
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,720
You'd be in competition with yourself.

34
00:01:18,510 --> 00:01:19,940
That's my favorite kind.

35
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:22,880
Okay, we are doing this.

36
00:01:23,270 --> 00:01:25,690
Don't let yourself get manipulated this way.

37
00:01:25,740 --> 00:01:27,090
Stay out of this, Chandler.

38
00:01:27,140 --> 00:01:29,230
This is between me and me.

39
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,080
We are supposed to

40
00:01:32,130 --> 00:01:33,670
make these decisions together.

41
00:01:34,890 --> 00:01:37,310
Dr. Phi:一档帮人解决家庭问题的脱口秀

42
00:01:34,890 --> 00:01:37,310
Did you not watch the <i>Dr. Phil</i> I taped for you?

43
00:01:39,580 --> 00:01:41,820
《老友记》第十季第八集 感恩节晚餐大家都迟到了

44
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:34,210
- Hey. - Hi. Happy Thanksgiving.

45
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:36,730
Happy Needless Turkey-Murder Day.

46
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:39,960
You guys, I ordered some chocolate pies

47
00:02:40,010 --> 00:02:41,540
from that bakery on Bleeker.

48
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:42,590
Could you pick them up for me?

49
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,400
You're not making the pies?

50
00:02:44,450 --> 00:02:45,900
I don't make chocolate pies.

51
00:02:45,950 --> 00:02:46,850
When I was younger,

52
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,010
I entered this pie-eating contest.

53
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:50,050
I ate so many

54
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:51,750
that the thought of them makes me sick.

55
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,630
Did you at least win the contest?

56
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:56,580
Two minutes, twelve pies and a part of one tin.

57
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,280
Okay, I'll see you guys at 4.

58
00:02:59,330 --> 00:03:00,340
Can't wait.

59
00:03:00,390 --> 00:03:02,720
This dinner is gonna be so great.

60
00:03:02,770 --> 00:03:04,980
In your face, last-year me.

61
00:03:06,970 --> 00:03:08,030
- Hey, Rach? - Yeah.

62
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,590
What's Emma doing today?

63
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,210
Well, let's see,

64
00:03:11,260 --> 00:03:14,100
I know that she has a meeting with her lawyer...

65
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:16,910
...and then she has to make a very big poop.

66
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:19,730
Why?

67
00:03:19,780 --> 00:03:22,320
Well, I want to enter her in a baby pageant.

68
00:03:22,370 --> 00:03:23,650
Oh, my God.

69
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:26,130
That's the creepiest thing I've ever heard.

70
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,590
Okay, but before you say no,

71
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,550
my friend Suzanne is entering her kid.

72
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:31,440
And compared to Emma,

73
00:03:31,490 --> 00:03:33,130
she's a real dog.

74
00:03:33,730 --> 00:03:36,160
Phoebe, all babies are beautiful.

75
00:03:36,210 --> 00:03:37,030
Oh, okay.

76
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:38,730
No. Phoebe,

77
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:41,740
just the idea of pitting one baby against another...

78
00:03:41,790 --> 00:03:42,990
...l mean, you know,

79
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,030
and judging who's cuter just for a trophy...

80
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,100
And a thousand dollars.

81
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:49,070
...is something I'm very interested in.

82
00:03:50,150 --> 00:03:52,780
Oh, please, do not tell Ross.

83
00:03:52,830 --> 00:03:53,790
He still believes that

84
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,600
what's on the inside is important.

85
00:03:55,650 --> 00:03:58,680
Okay. And Emma needs a cowgirl outfit

86
00:03:58,730 --> 00:03:59,880
for the competition.

87
00:03:59,930 --> 00:04:02,640
Where am I gonna get a cowgirl outfit on Thanksgiving?

88
00:04:02,690 --> 00:04:03,910
Well, I was thinking--

89
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,470
Take the clothes off Joey's Cabbage Patch Kid!

90
00:04:16,450 --> 00:04:18,300
Did someone drop the baton again?

91
00:04:18,350 --> 00:04:20,280
Why come all the way from Kansas

92
00:04:20,330 --> 00:04:21,380
to do that?

93
00:04:24,590 --> 00:04:27,170
I don't get older, I just get better.

94
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,130
You know what just occurred to me?

95
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:31,700
This could be our last Thanksgiving

96
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:32,930
just the two of us.

97
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:35,260
I mean, we could be getting a baby soon.

98
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,170
You don't know that.

99
00:04:36,220 --> 00:04:37,840
Somebody's gonna pick us.

100
00:04:37,890 --> 00:04:38,980
But we haven't heard a thing

101
00:04:39,030 --> 00:04:40,800
from the adoption agency.

102
00:04:40,850 --> 00:04:42,990
I'm telling you, it's gonna happen.

103
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,000
Next year,

104
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:46,970
it's gonna be you, me and little Hemingway Bing.

105
00:04:49,010 --> 00:04:50,660
What? He's my favorite author.

106
00:04:50,710 --> 00:04:52,060
Name one of his books.

107
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,070
<i>The Firm</i>?

108
00:05:01,030 --> 00:05:03,550
Okay, let's see. Okay, the turkey's in the oven.

109
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,790
The stuffing is ready.

110
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:05,340
You know,

111
00:05:05,390 --> 00:05:07,580
you always cook this meal all by yourself.

112
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:08,990
Let me help this year.

113
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,730
Oh, Chandler, that's sweet.

114
00:05:10,780 --> 00:05:13,560
But you don't have to do everything Dr. Phil tells you to do.

115
00:05:14,530 --> 00:05:16,570
I'm serious, let me do something.

116
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:19,670
Just not the turkey. Nothing high-profile.

117
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,440
Okay, let's see.

118
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:23,070
Oh, the cranberry sauce.

119
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:23,910
It's easy to make,

120
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,570
and no one really cares about it.

121
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:27,910
Tell me more.

122
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:30,700
I'm gonna go check on something across the hall.

123
00:05:30,750 --> 00:05:32,480
You start by washing these.

124
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:36,380
Not with soap!

125
00:05:40,460 --> 00:05:44,120
You obviously haven't tasted my Palmolive potatoes.

126
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:48,070
Hi. Hey, guess what Joey has.

127
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,100
Three tickets to today's Rangers game!

128
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:52,070
Dude, I wanted him to guess.

129
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,080
Oh, my God.

130
00:05:54,130 --> 00:05:55,820
Yeah, they're great seats too.

131
00:05:55,870 --> 00:05:56,660
Guess where they are.

132
00:05:56,710 --> 00:05:57,560
Center ice.

133
00:05:59,780 --> 00:06:01,840
Did I do something to you?

134
00:06:04,190 --> 00:06:05,590
The game's at 1.

135
00:06:05,590 --> 00:06:06,280
So?

136
00:06:06,330 --> 00:06:08,060
Dinner's at 4. We'll never make it back.

137
00:06:08,110 --> 00:06:09,350
So we'll leave before it's over.

138
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,170
We'll be back in time.

139
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,020
You said that now.

140
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:13,280
But it could take us a long time to get back home.

141
00:06:13,330 --> 00:06:14,620
Plus, Joey could get lost

142
00:06:14,670 --> 00:06:16,940
and they could have to page us to go pick him up.

143
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:20,710
Dude, two times that happened!

144
00:06:22,420 --> 00:06:24,810
Look, Monica's been working hard all day.

145
00:06:24,860 --> 00:06:26,690
She didn't want to host in the first place.

146
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:27,770
We shouldn't go.

147
00:06:27,910 --> 00:06:29,270
He's right, man.

148
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:31,590
Yeah, I guess. So we'll see you at 4.

149
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:32,210
Okay.

150
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:33,350
And get ready to taste

151
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:35,220
my very special cranberries.

152
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:38,770
Or should I say "Chan-berries"?

153
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:44,710
That's some gentle comedy, dude.

154
00:06:46,580 --> 00:06:48,320
We're still going to the game, right?

155
00:06:48,370 --> 00:06:49,120
Yeah.

156
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:58,660
Hey.

157
00:06:58,710 --> 00:07:00,370
Phoebe, listen, I think we gotta go.

158
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:01,950
This place is freaking me out.

159
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,410
I've been watching this guy over there.

160
00:07:03,460 --> 00:07:05,070
I don't think he came with a kid.

161
00:07:06,070 --> 00:07:07,650
But we can't leave now.

162
00:07:07,700 --> 00:07:09,200
There was this one baby, Haley,

163
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:10,120
who was favored to win...

164
00:07:10,170 --> 00:07:12,270
...she got croup, so she had to stay home.

165
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:15,050
This competition just blew wide-open, folks.

166
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:18,050
Phoebe, it's just too weird.

167
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:20,730
I just saw a 1 -year-old with pantyhose on.

168
00:07:20,780 --> 00:07:23,150
Oh, I know. We should've been more prepared.

169
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:26,820
It's okay. Now, the way I see it,

170
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:29,310
our real competition now is Cameron.

171
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:31,350
My God, they just took her sweater off.

172
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,530
Michelin Man:著名轮胎的卡通形象

173
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,530
Look at those arms. Hello, Michelin Man.

174
00:07:33,580 --> 00:07:35,920
Phoebe, come on.

175
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:37,750
You know what, it's already 3:00.

176
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,440
They haven't even gotten to Emma's group yet.

177
00:07:39,490 --> 00:07:40,890
We got dinner.

178
00:07:40,940 --> 00:07:42,380
But Emma's got what it takes.

179
00:07:42,430 --> 00:07:43,660
She could go all the way!

180
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:48,500
Phoebe, you have to calm down.

181
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:49,920
Okay.

182
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:53,600
Rachel, the hottest babies in the tri-state area

183
00:07:53,650 --> 00:07:55,980
are in this room right now.

184
00:07:57,690 --> 00:07:59,380
I overheard a judge say

185
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:01,420
that not one of them holds a candle to Emma.

186
00:08:01,730 --> 00:08:03,190
- Really? - Yeah.

187
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,860
You heard him say that?

188
00:08:04,910 --> 00:08:05,650
Yeah.

189
00:08:06,150 --> 00:08:08,240
All right. Okay. All right,

190
00:08:08,290 --> 00:08:10,460
let's give these babies something to cry about.

191
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:13,140
Good. Let's get down to business.

192
00:08:13,190 --> 00:08:14,370
Emma needs some makeup.

193
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:15,500
What?

194
00:08:15,550 --> 00:08:18,210
She's gonna look washed-out next to the others.

195
00:08:18,260 --> 00:08:20,660
No, Phoebe, I'm not letting you put makeup on my baby.

196
00:08:20,710 --> 00:08:21,430
Why not?

197
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,850
Because I already did.

198
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:33,920
You suck! Get off the ice, you idiot!

199
00:08:34,930 --> 00:08:37,150
- What a game. - I know. Yeah.

200
00:08:37,770 --> 00:08:39,640
I can't believe Chandler's missing this.

201
00:08:39,690 --> 00:08:41,010
I'm sorry he's not here.

202
00:08:41,060 --> 00:08:41,950
But I gotta say,

203
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,390
I am really enjoying nacho chair.

204
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:47,080
Yeah, I'd probably enjoy it more

205
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:49,040
if you didn't keep batting my hand away.

206
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,220
These seats are great.

207
00:08:53,270 --> 00:08:54,220
I know, I know.

208
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:56,500
When I was here for "Holidays on lce" ...

209
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,490
...l was sitting so far away,

210
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:01,910
Michelle Kwan couldn't read my banner.

211
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:01,910
Michelle Kwan:花样滑冰世界冠军

212
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:04,450
We'd better get going.

213
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:05,880
If we don't leave now, we're gonna be late.

214
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,530
But it's a tie game.

215
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:08,910
So we're a little late.

216
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,330
The girls will be there.

217
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:12,460
Let's just stay for one more goal.

218
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,130
- I don't know. - One more fight.

219
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:15,390
- Okay. - Okay.

220
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,050
Where is everybody?

221
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,260
They're 45 minutes late.

222
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:23,940
I can't believe they're not here.

223
00:09:23,990 --> 00:09:26,450
I slave and I slave for what?

224
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:29,690
They've ruined Cranberry Day.

225
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:33,290
How late are we?

226
00:09:33,290 --> 00:09:34,130
Forty-five minutes.

227
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:36,480
- Here. - Okay.

228
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:39,070
Rachel and Phoebe are already there,

229
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,320
so they probably started without us.

230
00:09:40,370 --> 00:09:41,660
We could just slip in,

231
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:43,130
and no one needs to know where we were.

232
00:09:45,130 --> 00:09:47,620
You may want to lose the foam finger.

233
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:49,580
Oh, no, no, no.

234
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:51,330
You just want to put it on your hand.

235
00:09:55,170 --> 00:09:57,260
You're not at Thanksgiving?

236
00:09:57,310 --> 00:09:59,000
No, we're late.

237
00:09:59,050 --> 00:10:00,580
What are you doing here?

238
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:02,020
We're late too.

239
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:03,980
We figured we could be late

240
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:05,600
because you'd be on time.

241
00:10:05,650 --> 00:10:07,860
Don't point that thing at me, Tribbiani.

242
00:10:08,740 --> 00:10:10,330
So nobody's here?

243
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:11,690
Monica's gonna kill us.

244
00:10:11,740 --> 00:10:12,920
Yeah, where were you?

245
00:10:12,970 --> 00:10:14,950
Yeah, what's with the trophy?

246
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,960
Well, we were at a spelling bee.

247
00:10:19,690 --> 00:10:21,040
And I won.

248
00:10:22,270 --> 00:10:23,840
You won an adult

249
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:26,450
Thanksgiving Day spelling bee?

250
00:10:26,970 --> 00:10:29,700
Yes. Y-E-S. Yes.

251
00:10:30,210 --> 00:10:32,100
Let me see this.

252
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:35,790
"Grand Supreme Little Darling, New York Division"?

253
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,210
That's me.

254
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:42,120
You entered Emma in a beauty pageant?

255
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:46,190
And it looks like she put makeup on her.

256
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:48,720
Wait a second...

257
00:10:48,770 --> 00:10:51,480
Where have I seen that cowgirl outfit before?

258
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:53,890
I can't believe this.

259
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:55,150
She's our daughter.

260
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,800
That you would treat her like some kind of show dog

261
00:10:57,850 --> 00:10:59,030
is inexcusable.

262
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,620
She won a thousand dollars.

263
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:02,980
So this is an annual thing?

264
00:11:06,770 --> 00:11:09,040
That's Alicia May Emory's outfit!

265
00:11:10,910 --> 00:11:12,530
Guys, there are people in there

266
00:11:12,580 --> 00:11:14,020
who are not getting any happier.

267
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:15,360
What are we gonna do?

268
00:11:15,410 --> 00:11:16,540
I don't know, you guys figure it out.

269
00:11:16,590 --> 00:11:17,770
I gotta put Emma down for a nap.

270
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:19,230
And, Rach, while you're in there,

271
00:11:19,230 --> 00:11:20,780
throw something on Alicia May.

